  "body": "Currently React.addons.update() helper does not support changes in array items.\nIs there some internal reason for which it has not been implemented yet?\n\nI would be great to be able to do something like this:\n\n``` javascript\nthis.state.photos = [\n  { src: 'photo1.jpg', caption: 'cool photo'},\n  { src: 'photo2.jpg', caption: 'super cool photo'}\n];\n\nvar changedPhotos = React.addons.update(this.state.photos, \n{ \n    // change second photo\n    1 : {\n        src : { $set: 'new_photo.jpg' } \n    }\n});\nthis.setState({ photos: changedPhotos });\n```\n",
